fields: What shall we eat for our meal?
You are good at playing the guitar!
ありがとうございます
I want to try it too.
Do you want to try it a little?
ゆうこちゃん！英語できる
Then, tell me (how to solve) this question.
ごめん。私も分かんない
Sorry. I don’t understand it either.
山田さん、ここやめるみたいです
It seems that Yamada-san is quitting this job.
ほんとですか？なんでですか？
Is that true? Why is it?
後で聞いてみましょう
to think (about, of), to think over, to ponder, to contemplate, to reflect (on), to meditate (on)
good, excellent, fine, nice, pleasant, agreeable
or something; something like; or whatever​
the other day, previously, before, earlier, recently
Adverb (fukushi), Noun, Noun which may take the genitive case particle 'no'
isn't it?, don't you think?, right?, surely, come on
skillful, skilful, skilled, good, expert, clever (expression, trick, etc.), apt, appropriate
right?, isn't it?, doesn't it?, don't you?, don't you think?
to do, to undertake, to perform, to play (a game), to study
Godan verb with ru ending, Transitive verb
want to ... do something, would like to ...
a little, a bit, a small amount, a few, some, slightly, somewhat
ちょっと考える。何がいいかな
I will think about it a little. What would be good?
この前も食べたじゃん
We had it the other day, right?
Then, let’s think of another one.
to be able (in a position) to do, to be up to the task
only, just, merely, simply, no more than, nothing but, alone
Godan verb with mu ending, Transitive verb
how, in what way, how about
to understand, to comprehend, to grasp, to see, to get, to follow
Godan verb with ru ending, Intransitive verb
to resign, to retire, to quit, to leave (one's job, etc.)
Noun, Noun which may take the genitive case particle 'no', Na-adjective (keiyodoshi)
to know, to be aware (of), to be conscious (of), to learn (of), to find out, to discover
Godan verb with ru ending, Transitive verb
after; later​
Noun, Noun which may take the genitive case particle 'no'
Godan verb with ku ending, Transitive verb
